SIMPLE: forefend
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forefend
<hw>Fore*fend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>forfenden</ets>; pref. <ets>for-</ets> + <ets>fenden</ets> to fend.
See <er>Fend</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To hinder; to fend off;
to avert; to prevent the approach of; to forbid or prohibit. See
<er>Forfend</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God <qex>forefend</qex> it should ever be recorded in our
history.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It would be a far better work . . . to <qex>forefend</qex> the
cruelty.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forefinger</ent>⟦br⟧
